ARABIC: أَيَحْسَبُ أَن لَّن يَقْدِرَ عَلَيْهِ أَحَدٌ

ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_0: Does he imagine that no one has power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_1: Does he think that no one has power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_2: Does he think that no one can overpower him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_3: Does He think that no one will ever have control over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_4: Does man think that no one will ever have power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_5: Does he think that none can overcome him
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_6: Does he think that no one has power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_7: What, does he think none has power over him,
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_8: Thinketh he that none hath power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_9: Does he think then that no one has power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_10: Deemest he that none will overpower him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_11: Does he suppose that no one will ever have power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_12: Thinketh he, that none hath power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_13: Thinks he that none can overcome him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_14: Does he think that none has power over him!
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_15: Does he think that no one has power over him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_16: Does he think that never will anyone overcome him?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_17: [90:5] Does he suppose, does the strong man of Quraysh, namely, Abū’l-Ashadd b. Kalada, presume, on account of his strength, that (an: softened in place of the hardened form, its subject omitted, that is to say, annahu) no one will have power over him? Yet God has power over him.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_18: (Thinketh he) does the disbelieving man think (that) because of his strength and force (none hath power over him?) i.e. Allah cannot seize and punish him.
